News and Press Releases



Home / News / PR News / News and Press Releases



Thaioil Wins Board of the Year Awards 2015
     Recently, Mr. Kurujit Nakornthap, Chairman of the Board, Thai Oil Public Company Limited (Third Left) was presented with the Board of the Year Awards for Distinctive Practices 2015 , from Mr. Krirk-Krai Jirapaet, Chairman of the Board of Directors of The Thai Institute of Directors Association (IOD) (Third Right) . This year the selection criteria were based on five areas: 1. board policy, 2. board members, 3. board structure, 4. board process and communications, 5. board performance. The ceremony was held at Renaissance Bangkok Ratchaprasong Hotel.
     This ceremony arranged by The Thai Institute of Directors Association (IOD) in collaboration with six leading private sector organizations namely, the Stock Exchange of Thailand (SET), the Thai Chamber of Commerce, the Federation of Thai Industries, the Thai Bankers' Association, the Thai Listed Companies Association and, the Federation of Thai Capital Market Organizations. This award recognizes companies for their efficient and effective operation, as well as, their commitment to transparency and fair treatment to all stakeholders in accordance with corporate governance principles.

Photo Show (from left) : Gen. Jiradej Mokkhasmit , Independent Director / Chairman of the Nomination and Remuneration Committee, Thai Oil Plc ; Mr. Atikom Terbsiri, Chief Executive Officer and President, Thai Oil Plc; Mr. Kurujit Nakornthap, Chairman of the Board, Thai Oil Plc; Mr. Krirk-Krai Jirapaet, Chairman of the Board of Directors of The Thai Institute of Directors Association (IOD) , Mr. Thaworn Phanichaphan, Independent Director /Member of Nomination and Remuneration Committee /Member of the Corporate Governance Committee, Thai Oil Plc ; Mr. Yongyut Jantararotai, Director /Member of the Corporate Governance Committee, Thai Oil Plc.

For editor
     Thaioil Group comprises of Thai Oil Public Company Limited, Thai Paraxylene Company Limited, Thai Lube Base Public Company Limited,Global Power Synergy Company Limited, Thaioil Power Company Limited, Thaioil Solvent Company Limited, Thaioil Marine Company Limited, Thaioil Ethanol Company Limited, Thaioil Energy Services Company Limited, LABIX Company Limited and TOP SPP Co., Ltd. the latest.
     Thai Oil Public Company Limited (TOP), established in 1961, is one of the leading integrated refinery and petrochemical companies in Asia Pacific. TOP businesses are structured as an integrated operation of long value chains in order to capture and maximize synergy value covering oil refining, aromatics production, lube base oil production, power generation, marine transportation, petroleum transportation via multi-product pipeline, marine transportation and related business, renewable energy business and its related products, solvent and chemical products business and high-level consultancy service in an area of oil refining and petrochemical technologies concerned with energy-related businesses.

Thaioil has been selected as member of Dow Jones Sustainability Indices 2014 (DJSI) for 3 Consecutive Years 
     In September 2015, Dow Jones Sustainability Indices (DJSI) as the international sustainability benchmark assessing the economic, environmental and social performances among global listed companies has selected Thai Oil Public Company Limited as member of DJSI for 3 consecutive years. Most of all, Thaioil has also been globally ranked as Energy Industry Group Leader, for 2 consecutive years which comprised of industries of coal & consumable fuels; energy equipment & services; oil & gas producer; and oil & gas storage & transportation.
     In January 2015, RobecoSAM has ranked Thaioil as number 1 global sustainability in the oil and gas industry and has also announced Thaioil as Gold Class for 2 consecutive years.
For more information, please contact:




Niramol Likitprathan
Korakoj Petburikul


Phone: 081-624-2991 
