Thai Petroleum Pipeline Company Limited (THAPPLINE)

			Thai Petroleum Pipeline Co., Ltd. engages in domestic petroleum transportation business via multi-product pipeline.



Commencement of Commercial Operation
1994


Business Type
Petroleum transportation via multi-product pipeline


Transportation Capacity
26,000 million liters/year


Types of Products Transported
Basic unleaded gasoline
			Regular unleaded gasoline
			Jet fuel and diesel fuel


Transportation R
Transport Petroleum products from Thaioil and Esso Refinery in Sriracha, Chonburi to Lam Luk Ka terminal in Pathumthani and Sao Hai terminal in Saraburi, totaling 255 kilometers. The project to connect the transportation system with the terminals at Suvarnabhumi Airport and Map Ta Phut is currently in progress.






