                        Company Snapshot :


Thai Oil Public Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the oil refining and distribution business in Thailand. It operates through Oil Refinery, Lube Base Oil Refinery, Petrochemical, Power Generation, Marine Transportation Services, Solvent, Ethanol, and Other segments. The company operates oil refinery that produces petroleum products, including gasoline, diesel/gas oil, jet fuel, kerosene, fuel oil, and liquefied petroleum gas; and a petrochemical plant that produces paraxylene, benzene, toluene, and mixed xylenes. It is also involved in the production and distribution of lube base oil, bitumen/asphalt, and other by-products, as well as special products, such as treated distillate aromatics extract and slack wax; operation of 118 megawatts 239 megawatts, and 1,039 megawatts of electricity power plants; generation of steam; marine transportation of petroleum and petrochemical products through tankers; and petroleum transportation through multi-product pipeline; and production and sale of sugarcane, cassava-based, and molasses-based ethanol. In addition, the company invests, manufactures, and distributes hydrocarbon solvents, chemical solvents, and other chemicals; manufactures and sells linear alkyl benzene and other related products; and provides marine transportation services for crew and utilities, as well as management and general services. Further, it provides consultancy services in the area of energy-related and petrochemical businesses. Thai Oil Public Company Limited is headquartered in Bangkok, Thailand.













